ANC Secretary General Ace Magashule says the party welcomes investigation against all forms of corruption, irrespective of who committed it. Magashule was responding to a question posed to him about the investigation of corruption at Estina farm in Free State during a briefing following an NEC meeting which took place in Centurion over the weekend. He also confirmed that there was a discussion about the President Jacob Zuma as a president of the country and that there were engagements between him and the ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa on how to best run the affairs of government.  No decision taken to remove President Jacob Zuma: Magashule | #ANCNEC #DSTV405 pic.twitter.com/2MyinvfWxz â€” ANN7 (@ANN7tv) January 22, 2018 Magashule announced that the ANC resolved to form interim structures to run ANC affairs in Free State and KwaZulu-Natal following the dissolution of both provincial leadership structures by the courts. Magashule also said it was a matter of public record that his son works for the Gupta family and that there was nothing wrong with that. -TNA Reporter